# 🔸 Decision Boundary
# Z = clf_svm.predict(...)
# ✔ What happens:
# Creates classification regions
# 📊 Plot Interpretation (VERY IMPORTANT)
# ✔ If clear separation:
# Model performs well
# ✔ If overlap:
# Hard to distinguish faults
# ✔ Curved boundary:
# Nonlinear relationships present
# 🧠 Discussion Example:
# 
# The PCA scatter plot shows partial overlap between classes, indicating that the features may not completely separate fault and normal conditions. The nonlinear SVM boundary suggests complex relationships within the dataset.
# 
