# ✔ Steps:
# Train model
# Predict output
# Evaluate performance
# 🔹 6. Evaluation Metrics
# ✔ Accuracy
# accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
# % of correct predictions
# ✔ Classification Report
# classification_report(y_test, y_pred)
# 
# Includes:
# 
# Precision
# Recall
# F1-score
# ✔ Confusion Matrix
# confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
# 📊 Interpretation (CRITICAL)
# Term	Meaning
# TP	Correct fault detection
# TN	Correct normal detection
# FP	False alarm
# FN	Missed fault ❗
# ⚠️ Industrial Insight (VERY IMPORTANT)
# 
# False Negatives are dangerous because they represent undetected faults, which may lead to system failure and safety hazards.
# 
# 🔹 7. ROC Curve
# roc_curve(y_test, y_score)
# ✔ Purpose:
# Evaluate model performance across thresholds
# ✔ AUC (Area Under Curve)
# auc(fpr, tpr)
# Value	Meaning
# 1.0	Perfect
# 0.5	Random
# 📊 Interpretation:
# Higher AUC → better model
# Curve near diagonal → poor model

# The machine learning pipeline demonstrates that different models perform variably depending on data characteristics. Random Forest typically provides robust performance due to its ensemble nature, while SVM captures nonlinear patterns effectively. The MLP model shows potential but may require further tuning.
# 
# The ROC curves indicate that models with higher Area Under Curve values provide better classification performance. However, in industrial applications, minimizing false negatives is more critical than maximizing overall accuracy.
# 
# Overall, this pipeline provides a comprehensive framework for fault detection and process optimisation in nanoelectronic systems.

